xvii To Aelius Lamia

ELIUS. from ancient Lamus sprung

Most nobly-for from him arose Lamiae of days both old and young, As written record clearly shows -

He who was founder of thy stem Held Formiae's walls and ruled, they say, Where Liris' brimming waters hem Marica’s shores, lord of wide sway.

To-morrow eastern winds will roar.
